1. Create an account on PiCloud
2. Create a new environment using Ubuntu 12.04
3. SSH to this environment and
   sudo apt-get install python-software-properties
   sudo add-apt-repository ppa:fenics-packages/fenics
   sudo apt-get update
   sudo apt-get install fenics
   sudo apt-get dist-upgrade
4. 


Run django on app engine
Somehow connect to Picloud and use answers

export PATH=/Applications/GoogleAppEngineLauncher.app/Contents/Resources/GoogleAppEngine-default.bundle/Contents/Resources/google_appengine/lib/django-1.4/django/bin:$PATH


Django on Heroku
----------------

mkdir foo
cd foo
virtualenv-2.7  venv --distribute --no-site-packages
source venv/bin/activate
pip install Django psycopg2 dj-database-url

